This paper discusses the issue of timing channels in microarchitectural features of processors, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the need for operating systems to partition or flush microarchitectural state, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses specific microarchitectural features such as CPU caches, TLBs, branch predictors, and prefetchers, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY).
